headline: Looking At The Narrative For Interactive Brokers Group IBKR After Crypto And Rate Shift
summary: Analysts have made a fine tune to their view on Interactive Brokers Group, trimming the fair value estimate from about US$77.33 to about US$76.89 per share while also adjusting the discount rate modestly lower from about 8.75% to about 8.68% and lifting revenue growth assumptions from about 6.56% to about 8.79%. These shifts reflect a tug of war between confidence in the company’s role in global electronic trading and fully automated brokerage, and caution around interest rate sensitivity and...
